Author: j01ene
Text: Yeah, I haven't felt the real hunger in years.. Not the "it's lunch time" or "I am bored" or "something salty would be nice rn", but the real hunger. I only noticed once when I was restricting low and working out (weight lifting), I couldn't lift even my warm-up weight and I basically was too exhausted to do even 8 reps. But that's it. My stomach growling shuts up after half an hour usually.   Tbh, I think, it's mental over physical war that has being won by an ED. I mean.. It is possible to convince yourself that you feel or don't feel something specific. And years of ED do that
